article.description: — Malevy Leons had 15 points in Bradley's 73-60 victory against Southeast Missouri State on Saturday night.
article.headline: Leons' 15 lead Bradley over Southeast Missouri State 73-60
article.linkText: Leons' 15 lead Bradley over Southeast Missouri State 73-60
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- — Malevy Leons had 15 points in Bradley's 73-60 victory against Southeast Missouri State on Saturday night. Leons had nine rebounds and four blocks for the Braves (3-1). Ville Tahvanainen shot 7 for 16, including 1 for 9 from beyond the arc to add 15 points. Duke Deen recorded 12 points and was 4 of 8 shooting, including 2 for 5 from distance, and went 2 for 3 from the line. Chris Harris finished with 14 points for the Redhawks (3-1). Phillip Russell added 13 points, seven assists and two steals for Southeast Missouri State. In addition, Kobe Clark had 10 points, nine rebounds and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
